RNAs are included.<\/p>\n\n<p>When we say poly(A)+ RNA library, what is the difference between normal one? Or normal RNA library is a poly(A)+ RNA library? Thanks.<\/p>\n","question_id":1965,"tags":["molecular-biology","rna"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":1967,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":2952,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1335482629},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2648f806f3af808a2ed537c8e745558e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":780,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/780/steven-jeuris","reputation":139,"display_name":"Steven Jeuris"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e1d3326342ee9de40822577d766465e8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":72,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/72/yamad","reputation":2340,"display_name":"yamad"},"score":7,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2648f806f3af808a2ed537c8e745558e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":780,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/780/steven-jeuris","reputation":139,"display_name":"Steven Jeuris"},"score":0,"post_id":1992,"edited":false,"creation_date":1335528560,"comment_id":2586,"body":"<i>&quot;I don&#39;t think I have ever observed dendritic loops&quot;<\/i> ... On the images it did look like a loop, but I&#39;ve noticed big staining gaps before. <i>&quot;do not look like a continuous structure&quot;<\/i> I don&#39;t know how the 3d model algorithm handles additions, and how much you can rely on it visually, although it does look like the structure is rounded prior to touching, which could indicate it&#39;s just a staining gap."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2648f806f3af808a2ed537c8e745558e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":780,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/780/steven-jeuris","reputation":139,"dis