cy and toughness, and a dry cuticle would be mechanically disastrous<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>So by maintaining a flexible tissue, insects have strong and tough wings that remain light enough.<\/p>\n","answer_id":1507,"question_id":1472,"up_vote_count":8}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/1472/why-dont-dragonflies-wings-collapse","last_activity_date":1332301025,"creation_date":1332035810,"answer_count":1,"title":"Why don't dragonflies wings collapse?","body":"<p>How do dragonflies manage to fly at such high speeds without their wings collapsing? Their wings are thinner than paper, but they do not even flutter. What gives them their strength?<\/p>\n","question_id":1472,"tags":["entomology","flight"],"score":10,"accepted_answer_id":1507,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":214,"up_vote_count":10},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fe87113ced5f370d038b90a43fd1fe1f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":408,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/408/anixx","reputation":909,"display_name":"Anixx","accept_rate":20},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/TVDAK.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":69,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/69/rory-m","reputation":9094,"display_name":"Rory M","accept_rate":88},"score":7,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fe87113ced5f370d038b90a43fd1fe1f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":408,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/408/anixx","reputation":909,"display_name":"Anixx","accept_rate":20},"score":1,"post_id":1467,"edited":false,"creation_date":1332013099,"comment_id":1825,"body":"still there are plants that feel well in water-flooded environment, as rice for example."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/52bddd6ae812be4933dc7d26c41d96af?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id"