pasy.org/\">ENZYME<\/a>, The Enzyme Data Bank. There you can search for chemical compounds. I did a search of coumarin and there are a few hits but they are for methyl-transferases and hydrolases. A more extensive search may give you a few leads.<\/p>\n\n<p>Most of the concepts that I just suggested are explained in the following review: <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18725289\">De novo biosynthetic pathways: rational design of microbial chemical factories.<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":1417,"question_id":1406,"up_vote_count":7}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/1406/is-there-an-enzyme-for-the-transformation-of-the-hydroxyl-group","last_activity_date":1331906198,"creation_date":1331637719,"answer_count":1,"title":"Is there an enzyme for the transformation of the hydroxyl group?","body":"<p>I would like to know, is there any enzyme which does the transformation of hydroxyl group to any other functional group using the enzyme. <\/p>\n\n<p>The substrate is aromatic hydroxyl group. Product should not have hydroxyl group.<\/p>\n\n<p>How should these types of queries be searched for?<\/p>\n","question_id":1406,"tags":["biochemistry","enzymes"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":1417,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":266,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1331906198},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/95f88f7c5f4fac6d14156c0100bdbc4d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":600,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/600/math4tots","reputation":185,"display_name":"math4tots"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/de2c4fd753821f85c74d886aa17410de?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":107,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/107/kmm","reputation":8486,"display_name":"kmm"},"score":0,"post_id":1424,"edited":false,"creation_date":1331784119,"comment_id":1765,"body":"Are you just asking how large is a typical cell?"},{"owner":